nature of=20
  concatenation. For example, if concat(sha1(message1), md5(message1)) =
=3D=3D=20
  concat(sha1(message2), md5(message2)) then sha1(message1) =3D=3D =
sha1(message2)=20
  and md5(message1)=3D=3Dmd5(message2). The concatenated function could =
have other=20
  problems that the strongest hash lacks -- for example, it might leak=20
  information about the message when the strongest component does not, =
or it=20
  might be detectably nonrandom when the strongest component is not -- =
but it=20
  can't be less collision-resistant.</SPAN></LI>
